 :arena: n. [common; Unix] The area of memory attached to a process by brk(2)
and sbrk(2) and used by malloc(3) as dynamic storage. So named from a malloc:
corrupt arena message emitted when some early versions detected an impossible
value in the free block list. see {overrun screw}, {aliasing bug}, {memory
leak}, {memory smash}, {smash the stack}.